<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-63-0078 </DOCNO><TEXT>The organizing principle for the conference on Dynamic Aspects of MicrotubuleBiology, and for this volume, is our understanding of the factors regulatingthe appearance and disappearance of microtubules in cells. All of thecontributions to this conference deal with aspects of this fundamentalfeature of cell biology. As a point of departure for considering theseproblems, some basic features of what is known about factors regulatingthe presence of microtubules in at least some cells will be reviewedin this chapter, which will serve as an introduction to the proceedingsof the conference.</TEXT></DOC>